WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:02.968
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>

00:02.970 --> 00:04.503
I'm emancipating from you.

00:04.505 --> 00:06.205
It's your damn daughter sinking
her fangs into my little girl.

00:06.207 --> 00:07.539
-Watch your mouth.
-[ grunts ]

00:07.541 --> 00:09.274
Rayna: I can't figure out how
to work through this.

00:09.276 --> 00:11.443
Just tell me what to do.
I will do it.

00:11.445 --> 00:13.645
I just got an offer
from a headphone company.

00:13.647 --> 00:15.047
They only want scarlett
for the commercial.

00:15.049 --> 00:17.816
Gunnar scott,
come on out onstage with me.

00:17.818 --> 00:19.151
I don't know about you,

00:19.153 --> 00:20.686
But I'd love to see
where this goes.

00:20.688 --> 00:22.788
I love you, ma.
[ cries ]

00:22.790 --> 00:25.357
<i> Being gay is not an issue --</i>
<i> certainly not for me.</i>
<i> Oh.</i>

00:25.359 --> 00:27.059
You have to stop
fighting will's battle for him.

00:27.061 --> 00:28.327
I'm on the right side
of history here.

00:28.329 --> 00:29.194
Goodbye, ken.

00:30.064 --> 00:32.998
¶¶

00:33.000 --> 00:35.501
[ cheers and applause ]

00:35.503 --> 00:37.669
He's a red-hot country artist

00:37.671 --> 00:40.906
Who just became one of the
hottest topics in the headlines,

00:40.908 --> 00:43.642
So you knew we had to make
some room for him at the table.

00:43.644 --> 00:44.877
Please welcome luke wheeler.

00:44.879 --> 00:46.145
Hey, luke!
Hey.

00:46.147 --> 00:47.513
[ cheers and applause ]
thanks for having me.

00:47.515 --> 00:48.647
Thank you.

00:48.649 --> 00:50.682
So, you're a hot topic
right now

00:50.684 --> 00:52.751
For your very heated
and very public battle

00:52.753 --> 00:55.587
With conservative pundit
cynthia davis.

00:55.589 --> 00:57.089
How'd this all start?

00:57.091 --> 00:58.557
Well, I wanted
to get my artist

00:58.559 --> 01:00.426
Will lexington's music
on the radio...
Right.

01:00.428 --> 01:02.694
...Uh, but we ran into
some resistance

01:02.696 --> 01:04.596
Because of
his sexual orientation.

01:04.598 --> 01:08.000
So I made a public plea
to have his song requested,

01:08.002 --> 01:09.902
And cynthia took offense.

01:09.904 --> 01:12.838
And she says
that you were shaming people

01:12.840 --> 01:14.573
Into feeling like a bigot.

01:14.575 --> 01:16.842
Well, um, cynthia says
a lot of things,

01:16.844 --> 01:18.544
A lot of which aren't true,

01:18.546 --> 01:21.213
But the truth is
that will is an amazing artist,

01:21.215 --> 01:23.348
And the conversation
should be about his music.

01:23.350 --> 01:26.051
Well, but regardless
what the conversation<i> should</i> be,

01:26.053 --> 01:28.687
The fact remains that it's not
about the music, really.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.956
I mean, you've shined a light on
a very important social issue.

01:30.958 --> 01:32.791
So what's your stance
on that?

01:32.793 --> 01:35.127
Well, I believe
that any discrimination --

01:35.129 --> 01:37.963
Whether it be race, religion,
or sexual orientation --

01:37.965 --> 01:39.765
Is just plain wrong.

01:39.767 --> 01:41.800
[ cheers and applause ]

01:41.802 --> 01:43.635
I couldn't agree
more,

01:43.637 --> 01:45.437
But here's where
I'm still confused.

01:45.439 --> 01:47.906
I mean, you're the forerunner
leading this charge.

01:47.908 --> 01:49.575
Where's lexington
in all this?

01:49.577 --> 01:52.044
Well, uh, will's gone through
a little personal tragedy.

01:52.046 --> 01:53.979
He just lost his mom,
so...

01:53.981 --> 01:56.482
But he was refusing to comment
even before that, right?

01:56.484 --> 01:59.451
I think the problem
that a lot of people have is,

01:59.453 --> 02:02.921
Why does it seem like
<i> you</i> care more than him?

02:02.923 --> 02:04.790
Well, I don't know
if it does seem like that,

02:04.792 --> 02:07.226
But I can assure you
that will cares.

02:07.228 --> 02:09.828
¶¶

02:09.830 --> 02:11.830
Hi. I'm dr. Voris.
Nice to meet you both.

02:11.832 --> 02:13.665
Hi. Thank you so much
for seeing us.

02:13.667 --> 02:14.766
And giving us
the whole day.

02:14.768 --> 02:16.401
Not a problem.

02:16.403 --> 02:18.470
I do occasionally,
when the situation requires it.

02:18.472 --> 02:19.805
We appreciate it.

02:19.807 --> 02:21.106
Come on in.

02:21.108 --> 02:23.175
¶¶

02:27.515 --> 02:28.881
[ knock on door ]

02:30.251 --> 02:32.618
Sorry.
Didn't mean to interrupt.

02:32.620 --> 02:33.952
No worries.

02:33.954 --> 02:35.154
The luggage is unloaded.

02:35.156 --> 02:36.622
We can drive home
whenever you're ready.

02:36.624 --> 02:38.023
Okay.

02:40.661 --> 02:41.927
Thank you.

02:41.929 --> 02:43.662
For what?

02:43.664 --> 02:46.031
For being exactly what I needed
these last couple days.

02:46.033 --> 02:47.466
[ chuckles ]

02:47.468 --> 02:49.101
I'm glad
my publicist sucks

02:49.103 --> 02:50.869
At finding me dates
for the red carpet.

02:50.871 --> 02:51.937
Me too.

02:51.939 --> 02:53.505
[ both chuckle ]

02:58.112 --> 03:00.445
Wait.

03:00.447 --> 03:02.881
Why don't you come with me
to new york?

03:02.883 --> 03:05.184
I mean, I'm taking your jet.
You might as well be on it.

03:05.186 --> 03:08.487
That is so tempting,
but I miss my little girl.

03:08.489 --> 03:10.355
I got to get back
to my real life.

03:11.392 --> 03:12.858
Mm.

03:12.860 --> 03:14.159
You have fun
in new york.

03:14.161 --> 03:15.561
I'll see you
at the oscars,

03:15.563 --> 03:17.563
And we'll pick up
right where we're leaving off.

03:17.565 --> 03:19.898
Yeah. Sure.

03:19.900 --> 03:22.334
Once scarlett and I wrap
the commercial shoot in chicago,

03:22.336 --> 03:24.670
You'll have some time off before
we join up again in orlando.

03:24.672 --> 03:26.038
I've got a couple
meet-and-greets

03:26.040 --> 03:27.639
And a morning spot
on magic 107.

03:27.641 --> 03:28.774
That work?

03:29.710 --> 03:31.410
-Yeah.
-Sure.

03:31.412 --> 03:33.145
Are we doing the "not talking
to each other" thing again?

03:33.147 --> 03:34.213
Look, whatever's best
for the band.

03:34.215 --> 03:35.581
You set it up,
we'll be there.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.082
Yep.
What she said.

03:37.084 --> 03:39.685
[ sighs ] okay.

03:39.687 --> 03:41.186
I'm gonna go finish
checking you out of your rooms.

03:41.188 --> 03:42.588
Thank you.

03:42.590 --> 03:44.489
Gunnar, can we please
just talk about --
hey, there.

03:44.491 --> 03:46.158
I don't know
about you two,

03:46.160 --> 03:49.828
But I could certainly use
a little break from this tour.

03:49.830 --> 03:51.163
You guys have plans?

03:51.165 --> 03:52.197
Uh, shooting a commercial
in chicago.

03:52.199 --> 03:53.332
Oh, that's right.

03:53.334 --> 03:55.067
Gunnar mentioned something
about that.

03:55.069 --> 03:56.501
That's so exciting for you.
Is that today?

03:56.503 --> 03:57.569
Yep.

03:57.571 --> 03:59.171
Aww! Bummer.

03:59.173 --> 04:01.006
I'm just on my way
to boston

04:01.008 --> 04:03.375
To see my old friend elton john
play a show,

04:03.377 --> 04:05.777
And I was gonna see
if you two wanted to tag along.

04:05.779 --> 04:08.247
Elton john? Seriously?
I love elton john.

04:08.249 --> 04:09.848
You're welcome to come.

04:09.850 --> 04:11.883
I mean, I know
I've offered before.

04:11.885 --> 04:14.453
Oh. Yeah, sure.
Got nothing else going on.

04:14.455 --> 04:15.954
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

04:15.956 --> 04:18.457
Sweet. My plane is waiting
for us whenever you're ready.

04:18.459 --> 04:19.524
Now's good.

04:19.526 --> 04:21.360
-Okay.
-Yeah? [ chuckles ]

04:21.362 --> 04:22.594
See ya.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.296
Have fun!

04:24.298 --> 04:26.465
All right.
Car's here.

04:26.467 --> 04:27.933
[ sighing ] okay.

04:27.935 --> 04:29.034
You okay?

04:30.137 --> 04:31.403
Yeah. I am.

04:31.405 --> 04:33.238
And we should get going.

04:33.240 --> 04:36.642
¶¶

04:36.644 --> 04:38.877
[ sighs ] okay.

04:38.879 --> 04:40.679
Yeah, thanks, dad.

04:42.216 --> 04:44.149
You guys talking now?

04:44.151 --> 04:47.319
Actually, he's called me twice
since I've been back.

04:47.321 --> 04:49.755
Even wants to send me
some of my mom's old things.

04:49.757 --> 04:51.156
Wow.

04:51.158 --> 04:52.658
Guess whatever
you said to him

04:52.660 --> 04:54.259
Must've really changed
his mind, huh?

04:54.261 --> 04:56.995
I don't know about that,
but...It's a start.

04:56.997 --> 04:58.163
[ cellphone rings ]

04:58.165 --> 05:00.565
Oh. Sorry.

05:00.567 --> 05:02.567
Hey, luke. What's up?
Hey, will.

05:02.569 --> 05:06.271
Just wanted to check in on you,
see how you're holding up.

05:06.273 --> 05:08.273
I imagine it's been
a hard couple days.

05:08.275 --> 05:10.609
Yeah, it's been rough,

05:10.611 --> 05:13.679
But, uh, I actually think
some good might come out of it

05:13.681 --> 05:14.680
With my father.

05:14.682 --> 05:16.181
I'm glad to hear that.

05:16.183 --> 05:18.684
Um, listen, you happen
to catch my appearance

05:18.686 --> 05:20.319
On "the view"
this morning?

05:20.321 --> 05:22.187
Oh! G-- I'm sorry.
I totally forgot.

05:22.189 --> 05:23.522
No, no.
It's no problem.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.123
It's just,
I want you to know

05:25.125 --> 05:28.927
That I'm committed as ever
to launching your album.

05:28.929 --> 05:31.697
Only...I can't do it
without<i> you.</i>

05:31.699 --> 05:33.632
Okay? I've got some appearances
lined up,

05:33.634 --> 05:35.600
And I'm gonna need you
out there with me.

05:35.602 --> 05:37.769
-I understand.
-Okay, good.

05:37.771 --> 05:39.838
I'll be back in nashville
in a few hours

05:39.840 --> 05:42.774
And, uh, have a radio interview
lined up for us later today,

05:42.776 --> 05:45.143
So why don't you meet me
back at the office

05:45.145 --> 05:46.845
And, uh, we can
discuss then, okay?

05:46.847 --> 05:48.814
Yes, sir.

05:48.816 --> 05:51.216
¶¶

05:55.889 --> 05:57.522
Hey.

05:57.524 --> 05:58.857
What are you doing here?

05:58.859 --> 06:01.293
I just wanted to clarify
what I meant in l.A.

06:01.295 --> 06:03.362
When I said, "I'd love to see
where this goes."

06:03.364 --> 06:04.896
Okay.

06:04.898 --> 06:07.466
Now, I-I didn't just mean
red carpets or hotel rooms,

06:07.468 --> 06:09.868
And honestly, I'd rather spend
more time with you here

06:09.870 --> 06:11.336
Than do
whatever crap my publicist

06:11.338 --> 06:13.038
Has scheduled for me
in new york.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.640
My life is so complicated
right now.

06:15.642 --> 06:17.042
That's never bothered me.

06:17.044 --> 06:18.810
But this will
never go anywhere

06:18.812 --> 06:21.546
If we don't really
get to know each other.

06:22.850 --> 06:24.816
So...What do you say?

06:27.388 --> 06:29.354
I say, "why not?"

06:29.356 --> 06:32.391
¶¶

06:34.661 --> 06:36.828
Yes, it was a mistake
for me to go to the bar.

06:36.830 --> 06:37.996
I said that, all right?

06:37.998 --> 06:39.164
But look,
me and frankie --

06:39.166 --> 06:41.199
We've been friends
for like 15 years.

06:41.201 --> 06:43.068
All of a sudden,
he is helping his daughter

06:43.070 --> 06:45.704
To basically
destroy our family.

06:45.706 --> 06:47.339
Is it crazy
for me to think

06:47.341 --> 06:48.840
That maybe we could have
a conversation about that

06:48.842 --> 06:49.908
Without him
physically assaulting me?

06:49.910 --> 06:51.209
It was stupid.

06:51.211 --> 06:52.778
It was a stupid thing
to do,

06:52.780 --> 06:55.180
And you didn't tell me about it
'cause you<i> knew</i> it was stupid,

06:55.182 --> 06:56.515
But you couldn't
help yourself!

06:57.851 --> 06:59.584
It's all just so familiar.

06:59.586 --> 07:02.354
This cycle just keeps repeating
itself over and over again --

07:02.356 --> 07:05.090
Betrayal, destruction,
abandonment, forgiveness.

07:05.092 --> 07:06.525
Yeah, 'cause that's what
I want to do.

07:06.527 --> 07:07.926
I want to get back
in that same cycle.

07:07.928 --> 07:10.295
Look, I would love
to be the guy

07:10.297 --> 07:11.797
That didn't make
the same mistake twice.

07:11.799 --> 07:13.298
I'm s--
-twice?!

07:14.802 --> 07:17.469
Deacon,
it's been a lifetime.

07:17.471 --> 07:21.807
Okay, okay. Let's, uh...
Let's stop and take a breath.

07:21.809 --> 07:24.776
There are clearly
very deep wounds here.

07:24.778 --> 07:28.113
¶¶

07:34.721 --> 07:36.288
See?

07:36.290 --> 07:38.123
I told you it'd be fun
cooking together.

07:38.125 --> 07:40.826
Yeah.
It totally is.

07:40.828 --> 07:43.295
So, this is really gonna
turn into spaghetti strands?

07:43.297 --> 07:44.663
Yeah, I mean, uh...

07:44.665 --> 07:46.231
Well, the texture's a little bit
different than pasta,

07:46.233 --> 07:47.632
But it's delicious.

07:47.634 --> 07:49.801
Oh.
It's also lower in calories
and cholesterol

07:49.803 --> 07:51.436
Than boxed pasta

07:51.438 --> 07:53.438
And higher in potassium,
calcium, and vitamins a and c.

07:53.440 --> 07:55.474
I mean, that's the best part
about cooking your own food,

07:55.476 --> 07:57.476
Is that you can control
your nutrition.

07:57.478 --> 07:59.578
You know, you can
supercharge your body.

07:59.580 --> 08:00.612
[ scraping ]

08:00.614 --> 08:01.713
Neat.

08:03.317 --> 08:05.150
I got you a gift
for tonight.

08:05.152 --> 08:06.785
What?!

08:06.787 --> 08:08.620
It's<i> your</i> album launch.

08:08.622 --> 08:10.655
You shouldn't be
getting me a gift.

08:10.657 --> 08:11.790
Oh.

08:11.792 --> 08:13.291
It's a -- it's a tie.

08:13.293 --> 08:15.827
It goes with my outfit
tonight.

08:15.829 --> 08:17.863
I thought it would be cute
if we coordinated.

08:17.865 --> 08:19.297
Right.
You know what?

08:19.299 --> 08:20.465
Never mind.
That's a lame idea.

08:20.467 --> 08:22.534
Hey, no.
It's -- it's a great idea.

08:22.536 --> 08:24.669
Really, I'm --
I'm happy to wear it.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.271
There's just so much
riding on tonight.

08:26.273 --> 08:28.173
I just want it
to be perfect.

08:28.175 --> 08:29.441
It<i> will</i> be.

08:29.443 --> 08:31.176
And I did get you something,
by the way...

08:31.178 --> 08:33.512
Sort of.
Really?

08:33.514 --> 08:36.348
Yeah, cadence is, uh,
spending the night at her mom's,

08:36.350 --> 08:39.718
So I'm yours...
All night.

08:40.854 --> 08:43.855
Did you know that elton john has
sold over 300 million records?

08:43.857 --> 08:46.024
And he's got six grammys,
a tony,

08:46.026 --> 08:48.159
A golden globe,
and an oscar.

08:48.161 --> 08:50.061
Has someone
been on wikipedia

08:50.063 --> 08:51.363
Since I went to get
the champagne?

08:51.365 --> 08:53.365
And the fact that he's stayed
on top for so long

08:53.367 --> 08:56.835
All by himself,
it's -- it's inspiring.

08:56.837 --> 08:59.237
Hey, what about<i> you?</i>

08:59.239 --> 09:02.040
How come you haven't...
Tried it by yourself?

09:02.042 --> 09:03.408
I don't know.

09:03.410 --> 09:05.310
Uh, I know
scarlett and I have our issues,

09:05.312 --> 09:09.180
But it's hard for me to imagine
doing it without her.

09:09.182 --> 09:12.050
Well...
Nothing lasts forever.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.718
But...

09:13.720 --> 09:15.921
That being said, you guys
are killing it right now,

09:15.923 --> 09:19.925
So there is no reason
for you not to just sit back

09:19.927 --> 09:21.760
And enjoy the moment.

09:24.197 --> 09:28.133
Kind of like how I'm enjoying
this one...With you.

09:29.403 --> 09:30.769
Yeah, me too.

09:30.771 --> 09:33.838
I think I've always been looking
for a healthier path.

09:33.840 --> 09:35.407
You know,
I think that's what

09:35.409 --> 09:37.542
The marriage with teddy
was about.

09:37.544 --> 09:39.611
I mean,
he was the anti-deacon.

09:39.613 --> 09:42.247
I think I was trying to build
a wall to protect myself,

09:42.249 --> 09:45.450
To protect my girls from...
My feelings for him.

09:45.452 --> 09:47.886
And yet it seems
you've built a door in that wall

09:47.888 --> 09:50.589
So you could let him in
or shut him out as you needed.

09:50.591 --> 09:52.424
I don't know
that I'd put it that way.

09:52.426 --> 09:54.192
Well, you had effectively
disentangled yourself

09:54.194 --> 09:55.594
From a romantic
relationship,

09:55.596 --> 09:57.862
Then you hired him
as your bandleader.

09:57.864 --> 09:59.230
Have you ever heard him
play guitar?

09:59.232 --> 10:01.132
And the songs
that we wrote together --

10:01.134 --> 10:03.568
Look, in spite of all the hell,
that part was heaven.

10:03.570 --> 10:05.236
There's just something
that happens.

10:05.238 --> 10:08.640
There's a magic
that happens.

10:08.642 --> 10:10.241
Still does.

10:10.243 --> 10:11.543
And you didn't want
to give that up.

10:11.545 --> 10:13.878
With deacon and me,
it's never about

10:13.880 --> 10:16.548
What we want
or what we don't want.

10:16.550 --> 10:19.317
I think
there's something...

10:19.319 --> 10:22.153
Really inevitable
about this relationship.

10:22.155 --> 10:25.123
It just feels like...

10:25.125 --> 10:27.659
We're inextricably tied.

10:28.729 --> 10:30.662
There's my angel!

10:30.664 --> 10:31.930
Hi!

10:31.932 --> 10:33.798
Ahh,
not so angelic today.

10:33.800 --> 10:35.634
She's teething
and really cranky.

10:35.636 --> 10:37.769
She woke up screaming twice
last night.

10:37.771 --> 10:39.437
Oh. I'm sorry.

10:39.439 --> 10:40.972
You cooking?

10:40.974 --> 10:42.240
Yeah.

10:42.242 --> 10:43.508
Well, sort of.

10:43.510 --> 10:45.744
Noah is here,
and he wanted to cook, so...

10:45.746 --> 10:48.413
Noah...West is here?

10:48.415 --> 10:51.416
Really? Wow.
That's -- that's fast.

10:51.418 --> 10:53.118
Well, not really.

10:53.120 --> 10:55.153
We've known each other
for a while.

10:55.155 --> 10:57.022
And you think it's --
it's all right

10:57.024 --> 10:59.124
For him to be around cadence
already?

10:59.126 --> 11:01.426
Avery, he's a good guy.

11:01.428 --> 11:03.461
And cadence is too young
to understand,

11:03.463 --> 11:05.430
Which is why
I've never had a problem

11:05.432 --> 11:06.998
With her spending time
with layla.

11:08.669 --> 11:09.968
Come on in.

11:09.970 --> 11:14.305
¶¶

11:14.307 --> 11:16.541
Hey, sweet girl.

11:16.543 --> 11:17.876
Oh, hey, man.

11:17.878 --> 11:19.711
Hi.

11:19.713 --> 11:21.279
Smells good.

11:21.281 --> 11:23.648
Yeah, just, uh,
heirloom tomato marinara.

11:23.650 --> 11:24.916
Yeah, you want a taste?

11:26.053 --> 11:27.218
No, thanks.

11:27.220 --> 11:28.820
All right.

11:28.822 --> 11:29.988
Uh, call me
if you need anything.

11:29.990 --> 11:31.890
Say "bye, daddy."

11:31.892 --> 11:33.024
-Bye.
-Say "bye, daddy.

11:33.026 --> 11:34.459
We'll be okay."

11:36.630 --> 11:38.129
This is my friend noah.

11:38.131 --> 11:39.531
Can you say "hi"?

11:39.533 --> 11:41.132
Oh, hey, there, cadence.
[ cadence cooing ]

11:41.134 --> 11:42.967
Hi. Oh.

11:42.969 --> 11:44.703
Your mama talks about you
all the time.

11:44.705 --> 11:46.638
[ chuckles ]

11:46.640 --> 11:48.039
Is kenneth
gonna join us?

11:48.041 --> 11:50.308
Uh, kenneth doesn't
work here anymore.

11:50.310 --> 11:51.910
What happened?

11:51.912 --> 11:54.646
I got enough resistance
out there to what we're doing.

11:54.648 --> 11:57.082
I don't need it coming
from within the label, as well.

11:57.084 --> 11:59.217
I'm sorry to hear that.
That's all right.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.252
I never liked him
that much anyway.

12:01.254 --> 12:03.321
Now, listen,
about this radio show --

12:03.323 --> 12:05.557
We got the spot because
the deejay's an old friend,

12:05.559 --> 12:07.392
And it's a mainstream
station.

12:07.394 --> 12:09.194
Is he gonna ask
about the controversy?

12:09.196 --> 12:11.262
Just a few questions
about your music,

12:11.264 --> 12:12.864
And then he's gonna play
the single.

12:12.866 --> 12:14.399
I just don't want to be
a spokesman, is all.

12:14.401 --> 12:16.768
No, don't worry about that.
I'll have your back.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.203
[ knock on door ]

12:18.205 --> 12:19.904
Luke, you have
an emergency call

12:19.906 --> 12:21.573
From the medical center
at fort benning.

12:23.343 --> 12:24.976
Excuse me one second,
will.

12:26.379 --> 12:27.545
[ telephone beeps ]

12:27.547 --> 12:28.947
This is luke wheeler.

12:28.949 --> 12:30.181
Yes, sir.

12:32.753 --> 12:34.619
U-um...

12:34.621 --> 12:36.788
Is he all right?

12:36.790 --> 12:38.089
Y-yes, sir.
Thank you.

12:38.091 --> 12:39.691
I-I'll be there
as soon as I can.

12:39.693 --> 12:40.792
Okay.
[ telephone beeps ]

12:40.794 --> 12:41.860
What is it?
Um...

12:41.862 --> 12:43.728
Colt was in an accident.

12:43.730 --> 12:45.096
I-I'm sorry, will.

12:45.098 --> 12:47.298
You're gonna have to do this
radio show on your own, okay?

12:47.300 --> 12:48.767
-Of course.
-Yeah.

12:48.769 --> 12:50.101
-Go take care of your son.
-Yeah.

12:55.075 --> 12:58.877
¶¶

12:58.879 --> 13:00.078
Sure you're all right?

13:00.080 --> 13:01.312
You barely said a word
on the plane.

13:01.314 --> 13:03.214
-Oh, I'm fine. Thank you.
-Scarlett.

13:03.216 --> 13:04.749
Dennis. Hi.
Head of promotion.

13:04.751 --> 13:07.418
We are excited to have you
as part of our ad campaign.

13:07.420 --> 13:09.821
Oh, I'm real excited to be here.
Thank you for having me.

13:09.823 --> 13:11.456
Well, I wanted to talk you
through the concept.

13:11.458 --> 13:14.893
Our theme is "cut out the noise,
what do you hear?"

13:14.895 --> 13:17.295
So, each one-sheet features
a different female artist

13:17.297 --> 13:19.297
Listening to her own music
on our headphones

13:19.299 --> 13:20.832
And answering
the question.

13:20.834 --> 13:22.300
Sounds really cool.

13:22.302 --> 13:24.435
Well, we've got "hope"
and "peace."

13:24.437 --> 13:27.438
For you,
we were thinking "joy."

13:27.440 --> 13:29.808
Would you stop, please?
Don't listen to him.

13:29.810 --> 13:32.443
Scarlett, this is jackie hudson,
our esteemed photographer.

13:32.445 --> 13:33.978
Hi.
That's right,
and I don't need you

13:33.980 --> 13:35.480
To tell her
what she should feel.

13:35.482 --> 13:37.282
I'm sure you can
figure that out on your own.

13:37.284 --> 13:38.783
Can't you?
-Yes, ma'am.

13:38.785 --> 13:40.685
Just listen to the music,
be honest,

13:40.687 --> 13:42.120
And we'll see
where that takes us.

13:42.122 --> 13:43.588
All right?

13:43.590 --> 13:45.023
All right.

13:45.025 --> 13:47.091
Deacon: I basically spent
most of my life

13:47.093 --> 13:50.862
Ashamed of the things
I'd done to myself, to...

13:50.864 --> 13:52.530
Other people, but...

13:54.868 --> 13:56.935
...Mostly to her.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.970
That's a very difficult way
to live,

13:58.972 --> 14:00.371
A tough thing to face.

14:00.373 --> 14:02.040
It's like
all I ever get to be

14:02.042 --> 14:03.541
Is the guy
who let her down again.

14:03.543 --> 14:04.776
You think
that's how she sees you?

14:04.778 --> 14:06.778
How else could she see me?

14:06.780 --> 14:10.481
You know, you talk a lot
about who you are to her.

14:10.483 --> 14:12.283
What about you?

14:12.285 --> 14:13.718
Who is<i> she</i> to<i> you?</i>

14:16.489 --> 14:17.889
[ exhales sharply ]

14:21.027 --> 14:23.061
She's everything.

14:26.333 --> 14:29.534
Without her...

14:29.536 --> 14:31.135
Music doesn't mean
anything.

14:31.137 --> 14:32.804
<i> Nothing</i> means anything.

14:34.808 --> 14:37.175
I've had to wrap my mind

14:37.177 --> 14:41.246
Around trying to live
without her...

14:41.248 --> 14:42.881
Too many times.

14:46.019 --> 14:48.686
I just don't know
if I can face that again.

14:48.688 --> 14:50.655
What if you had to?

14:50.657 --> 14:52.223
What would you do?

14:53.560 --> 14:54.959
Wait.

14:58.231 --> 14:59.430
[ sighs ]

14:59.432 --> 15:01.900
We're here today with
country star will lexington.

15:01.902 --> 15:03.601
Man, it's, uh, good
to have you here.

15:03.603 --> 15:05.103
Thank you for having me.
Absolutely.

15:05.105 --> 15:06.437
Uh, so, listen,

15:06.439 --> 15:09.207
What a roller coaster of
a career this has been for you.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.276
I mean, to be nominated
for a cma,

15:11.278 --> 15:13.244
You signed a record deal
with luke wheeler,

15:13.246 --> 15:14.913
Only to then be dropped
by luke,

15:14.915 --> 15:16.614
Then to re-sign with him,

15:16.616 --> 15:18.082
And now you're rolling out
a new album.

15:18.084 --> 15:19.617
It's exhausting
even just saying it all.

15:19.619 --> 15:21.686
[ chuckles ]
yeah, it's been quite a ride,

15:21.688 --> 15:23.888
But, uh, I think it's made me
a stronger artist,

15:23.890 --> 15:25.790
Both from a writing
and performing standpoint.

15:25.792 --> 15:27.225
Yeah, I hear that.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.360
There's so much emotional depth
to this.

15:29.362 --> 15:32.230
It's like a real step forward,
I think, from your first album.

15:32.232 --> 15:34.532
Thank you.
I appreciate you saying so.

15:34.534 --> 15:35.767
Now I got to ask,

15:35.769 --> 15:38.536
The experience of coming out
as a gay country artist,

15:38.538 --> 15:41.706
Did that have any kind of
an impact on this progression?

15:41.708 --> 15:45.376
Um...I don't know.

15:45.378 --> 15:47.645
I mean, um...

15:47.647 --> 15:50.448
So, what about the impact you're
having on the gay community?
[ sighs ]

15:50.450 --> 15:52.317
I can't speak
for anyone else.

15:52.319 --> 15:54.485
All I know is that
I'm real proud of this album.

15:54.487 --> 15:55.753
You should be.
Here it is.

15:55.755 --> 15:57.922
First taste of the new single
from will lexington.

15:57.924 --> 15:59.557
The song's called
"spinning revolver."

15:59.559 --> 16:01.926
[<i> "spinning revolver" plays</i> ]

16:01.928 --> 16:04.929
¶<i> well, a heart</i> ¶

16:04.931 --> 16:08.399
¶<i> it's a fragile thing,</i>
<i> hangin' on a string</i> ¶

16:08.401 --> 16:09.934
Hey!
Hey.

16:09.936 --> 16:11.436
Oh, my god.
Look at the turnout.

16:11.438 --> 16:12.971
Yeah. Way more press
than we expected.

16:12.973 --> 16:14.939
Just got a call from bucky,
though.

16:14.941 --> 16:17.008
Rayna can't make it --
family emergency.

16:17.010 --> 16:18.309
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.
Yeah.

16:18.311 --> 16:19.844
Well, maybe it's not
the worst thing

16:19.846 --> 16:21.179
That she's not here
to overshadow me.

16:21.181 --> 16:22.780
-Hey, there.
-Hi.

16:22.782 --> 16:24.515
-You look beautiful.
-Hi. Thank you.

16:24.517 --> 16:26.918
-Hey.
-Hey, nice tie.

16:26.920 --> 16:28.653
You ready to do this?

16:28.655 --> 16:30.955
Absolutely.

16:30.957 --> 16:33.992
[ crowd clamoring,
camera shutters clicking ]

16:40.266 --> 16:41.699
Something wrong?

16:41.701 --> 16:43.634
You're not having second
thoughts about this, are you?

16:43.636 --> 16:45.470
No. Just worried
about cadence.

16:45.472 --> 16:47.472
Was she still fussy?

16:47.474 --> 16:51.275
Well, that, and when I dropped
her off at juliette's,

16:51.277 --> 16:52.677
Noah west was there.

16:52.679 --> 16:54.045
Oh.

16:54.047 --> 16:55.113
Did that bother you?

16:56.282 --> 16:57.515
No.

16:57.517 --> 17:00.351
No, I just don't want juliette
to be distracted.

17:00.353 --> 17:01.953
It's gonna be fine.

17:01.955 --> 17:03.187
You know how I know?

17:03.189 --> 17:04.956
Because tonight
is gonna be perfect.

17:04.958 --> 17:06.124
Remember?

17:06.126 --> 17:07.892
[ chuckles ]

17:07.894 --> 17:09.660
Woman:
Layla! Over here!

17:09.662 --> 17:11.362
Hi.

17:11.364 --> 17:14.699
¶¶

17:14.701 --> 17:16.567
[ monitor beeping ]

17:21.808 --> 17:24.242
Been expecting you.

17:24.244 --> 17:26.911
His mother's
flying in tomorrow.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.312
Is he conscious?

17:28.314 --> 17:30.515
Pain meds got him knocked out
right now.

17:30.517 --> 17:32.216
Got a real bad
concussion,

17:32.218 --> 17:34.852
Broken arm,
plus quite a few stitches.

17:34.854 --> 17:36.854
[ sighs ]
what happened?

17:36.856 --> 17:39.223
Well, apparently, he got jumped
by a couple other recruits.

17:39.225 --> 17:40.224
Why?

17:40.226 --> 17:41.492
On account
of all that noise

17:41.494 --> 17:43.227
You've been making
in the press lately.

17:43.229 --> 17:47.165
Things kind of escalated
from there, and here we are.

17:47.167 --> 17:49.967
So, to answer your question,
this happened because of<i> you.</i>

18:01.548 --> 18:04.749
So...

18:04.751 --> 18:07.185
There are a couple of things
in play here.

18:08.922 --> 18:13.124
Deacon, you feel a great sense
of guilt and remorse

18:13.126 --> 18:15.593
About your alcoholism,
injuries to your wife.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.562
Losing our daughter.

18:17.564 --> 18:21.065
And, rayna, is it fair to say
that you have a history with men

18:21.067 --> 18:23.234
Who, in one way or another,
have disappointed you?

18:23.236 --> 18:26.404
Your father --
neglectful, controlling.

18:26.406 --> 18:29.607
Deacon -- unreliable,
sometimes volatile.

18:29.609 --> 18:31.309
Are you trying to say
I've<i> chosen</i> this?

18:31.311 --> 18:34.445
I'm not talking about choices --
just patterns.

18:34.447 --> 18:37.215
And as a result, you've had to,
as you said, build a wall.

18:37.217 --> 18:39.617
And, deacon,
to some degree,

18:39.619 --> 18:42.587
You have always seen rayna
as an unattainable ideal.

18:42.589 --> 18:45.790
So I would posit
that the work now would be

18:45.792 --> 18:48.092
For you, deacon,
to find a way

18:48.094 --> 18:51.262
To be relieved of
that crippling burden of guilt

18:51.264 --> 18:53.731
And for you, rayna,
to find a way

18:53.733 --> 18:55.867
To take a step
towards forgiveness.

18:57.504 --> 19:01.105
You both have a deep mythology
about this bond --

19:01.107 --> 19:03.007
Its inevitability,

19:03.009 --> 19:05.243
The sense of yourselves
as artists

19:05.245 --> 19:07.578
All tied up within it.

19:07.580 --> 19:09.780
But there's a dark side
to it.

19:09.782 --> 19:11.582
I'm not questioning whether
you both love each other or not.

19:11.584 --> 19:13.584
You clearly do.

19:13.586 --> 19:16.921
But the tough question
you have to answer is,

19:16.923 --> 19:19.757
What are you both getting
out of this relationship?

19:19.759 --> 19:21.893
¶¶

19:33.606 --> 19:35.540
¶<i> come on, honey,</i>
<i> stay a little longer</i> ¶

19:35.542 --> 19:37.608
All right, with this song,
what do you hear?

19:37.610 --> 19:39.977
Cheer. Glee. Fun.

19:39.979 --> 19:42.146
No, what do you hear?
What do you feel?

19:42.148 --> 19:43.881
Happiness?

19:45.018 --> 19:48.186
You're smiling, but your eyes
are giving you away.

19:48.188 --> 19:50.488
I don't see happy.
I see fear.

19:50.490 --> 19:51.989
Uh...

19:51.991 --> 19:54.125
Well, m-maybe if you just tell
me what you would like me to do,

19:54.127 --> 19:55.693
I could just do that.

19:55.695 --> 19:58.296
This isn't about what<i> I</i> want.
This is about<i> you.</i>

19:58.298 --> 20:00.464
This is about
<i> your</i> feelings.

20:00.466 --> 20:02.033
Well, the truth is,
I-I do feel happy

20:02.035 --> 20:03.668
When I'm listening
to my music.

20:03.670 --> 20:07.038
I'm just really sorry that it's
not coming through properly.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.206
All right,
cut the music!

20:08.208 --> 20:09.240
[ click, music stops ]

20:09.242 --> 20:11.842
Clear the room!
Everyone out!

20:11.844 --> 20:14.412
And leave me the controls
for the music.

20:14.414 --> 20:17.582
[ people murmuring ]

20:17.584 --> 20:19.517
Perhaps now
you can stop hiding.

20:19.519 --> 20:21.385
[ door closes ]

20:23.356 --> 20:25.223
Autumn: Gunnar? Hey!

20:25.225 --> 20:27.592
I'd like you to meet
my friend elton john.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.360
Hey, how are you?
Great to meet you.

20:29.362 --> 20:30.561
Hi. Big fan.

20:30.563 --> 20:32.230
I mean, that is, of -- of<i> you.</i>
[ chuckles ]

20:32.232 --> 20:34.932
Well, me too,
because autumn slipped me

20:34.934 --> 20:37.602
A couple of tracks and some
video clips from the tour,

20:37.604 --> 20:39.837
And I have to say,
it's absolutely fantastic.

20:39.839 --> 20:41.372
Well done.

20:41.374 --> 20:43.241
He was particularly impressed
with the song

20:43.243 --> 20:44.742
You and I did
at last night's show.

20:44.744 --> 20:46.010
Yeah.
That is a great song.

20:46.012 --> 20:47.111
Well, thank you.

20:47.113 --> 20:48.246
I'm gonna ask you
a question now.

20:48.248 --> 20:49.180
Yeah.

20:49.182 --> 20:50.348
Have you heard
my new record?

20:50.350 --> 20:51.949
Yeah. It's amazing.
Oh, thank you very much.

20:51.951 --> 20:53.951
And what is your favorite song
on the record?

20:53.953 --> 20:55.953
Uh, well, I got to say
"blue wonderful."

20:55.955 --> 20:57.555
Right.
Well, "blue wonderful" it is.

20:57.557 --> 20:59.724
You're gonna come and sing it
with me onstage tonight, okay?

20:59.726 --> 21:02.460
Uh...I'd be honored.
[ chuckles ]

21:02.462 --> 21:03.745
Get this guy a guitar,

21:03.746 --> 21:05.029
And let's get the hell
out of here and go onstage.

21:05.031 --> 21:06.464
Come on. Here we go.
-Okay.

21:06.466 --> 21:07.865
-Come on, gunnar.
-Oh, my g-- [laughs]

21:13.273 --> 21:14.438
[ sighs ]

21:18.778 --> 21:20.544
Daphne gonna be there
when we get home?

21:20.546 --> 21:23.114
No.

21:23.116 --> 21:25.182
She's spending the night
at simone's.

21:29.822 --> 21:31.255
[ cheers and applause ]

21:31.257 --> 21:32.923
Thank you all for coming.

21:32.925 --> 21:35.626
Highway 65
could not be more excited

21:35.628 --> 21:37.495
About this terrific
young artist.

21:37.497 --> 21:39.730
You may think
you know her already,

21:39.732 --> 21:42.300
Because she's been in the public
eye, but this new album...

21:42.302 --> 21:44.835
I wish he'd wrap it up.
I'm ready to sing.

21:44.837 --> 21:47.905
...The real layla grant,
and you better get ready,

21:47.907 --> 21:49.340
'cause she's about to
take over the world.

21:49.342 --> 21:50.741
Ladies and gentlemen,

21:50.743 --> 21:53.811
Please help me welcome
the amazing ms. Layla grant.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.579
[ cheers and applause ]

21:55.581 --> 21:58.149
Hi, everyone.

21:58.151 --> 22:00.284
Thanks, bucky, for not setting
the expectations too high.

22:00.286 --> 22:02.186
[ chuckles ]

22:02.188 --> 22:03.854
You guys ready
to hear some music?

22:03.856 --> 22:07.124
[ "soul survivor" plays ]

22:07.126 --> 22:11.829
¶ how do you
turn a sinkin' ship ¶

